       #include <lber.h> #include <ldap.h>

       int ldap_simple_bind(LDAP *ld, char *who, char *passwd);

       int ldap_simple_bind_s(LDAP *ld, char *who, char *passwd);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       These routines provide an interface to the LDAP bind oper-
       ation using simple or no authentication. After an associa-
       tion is made to an LDAP server using or an LDAP bind oper-
       ation  must  be  performed  before other operations can be
       attempted over the conection.

       Simple authentication, if used, sends a cleartext password
       to the LDAP server.

       The  ld  parameter  is  the  LDAP  session  identifier  as
       returned from ldap_init or ldap_open.

       The who parameter is the DN (distinguished  name)  of  the
       user  being  authenticated. For an anonymous bind, the who
       parameter may be set to NULL or to a  pointer  to  a  null
       string ("").

       The  passwd  parameter is the password associated with the
       user.  If no password is required or an anonymous bind  is
       being  performed,  the  passwd  parameter should be set to
       NULL or to a pointer to a null string ("").

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       ldap_simple_bind returns the message ID of the request  it
       sent.  The  result  of  the operation can be obtained by a
       subsequent call to If ldap_simple_bind fails,  it  returns
       -1.

       ldap_simple_bind_s  returns  LDAP_SUCESS  upon  successful
       completion, otherwise an LDAP error  indication  (see  for
       details).

